# Canonical rsync exclusion list for `make deploy`.
#
# Any rsync that ships this repo to prod MUST pass --exclude-from=.rsync-exclude.
# Every entry here is either a secret, prod-only runtime state, or a binary
# artifact that would corrupt a deploy if erased by `--delete`.
#
# History: two incidents in 2026 (Phase 7 wiped .env.production, Phase 9 wiped
# probe-pay.macaroon) were caused by ad-hoc rsync commands that forgot one of
# these exclusions. Keep this list authoritative — never hand-type excludes
# into an ad-hoc rsync call.
#
# Patterns without a leading slash match at any depth.
# See docs/DEPLOY.md for the deploy procedure.

# ── Secrets (MUST never leave the local machine) ─────────────────────────
.env
.env.local
.env.production
.env.*.local

# ── Prod-only runtime state (MUST never be overwritten from local) ───────
data/
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite-journal
*.sqlite-shm
*.sqlite-wal
backups/

# ── Macaroons: LND credentials baked on prod. Never shipped from local. ──
# Covers probe-pay.macaroon, admin.macaroon, invoice.macaroon, readonly.macaroon.
*.macaroon

# ── L402/Aperture config (prod-only, references secrets) ─────────────────
aperture.yaml
aperture.local.yaml

# ── Build artifacts (rebuilt on prod inside Docker) ──────────────────────
node_modules/
dist/
build/

# ── Python SDK build/cache (do NOT ship venv or bytecode) ────────────────
python-sdk/.venv/
python-sdk/build/
python-sdk/dist/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo

# ── SDK node_modules (shipped to prod via its own build step) ────────────
sdk/node_modules/
sdk/dist/

# ── Git / IDE / Claude / local noise ─────────────────────────────────────
.git/
.github/
.vscode/
.idea/
.DS_Store
.claude/
*.swp
*.swo
coverage/

# ── Log files (prod writes to /var/log/satrank, not the app dir) ─────────
*.log
logs/
